<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
During a school fundraising event, tickets were sold in two groups. The first group sold <m>x</m> tickets, while the second group sold <m>x + {6}</m> tickets. Altogether, <m>{72}</m> tickets were sold.
</p>

<p>
(a) Form a quadratic equation representing this situation.
</p>

<p>
<alert>Equation</alert> <fillin characters="15" name="eqn1"/>  
</p>

<p>
(b) Determine the value of <m>x</m>.
</p>

<p>
<m>x =</m> <fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Let the number of tickets sold by the first group be <m>x</m>.
</p>

<p>
The second group sold <m>x + {6}</m> tickets.
</p>

<p>
The total number of tickets sold was <m>{72}</m>.
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Form the equation.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x(x + {6}) = {72}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Expand the expression.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 + {6}x = {72}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Rearrange the equation into standard quadratic form.
</p>

<p>
<me>
x^2 + {6}x - {72} = 0
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Factorise the quadratic expression.
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x - {6})(x + {12}) = 0
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 5: Solve each factor.
</p>

<p>
First factor:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x - {6} = 0
</me>
</p>

<p>
Add <m>{6}</m> to both sides:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x = {6}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Second factor:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x + {12} = 0
</me>
</p>

<p>
Subtract <m>{12}</m> from both sides:
</p>

<p>
<me>
x = -{12}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Since the number of tickets sold cannot be negative, we reject the negative solution.
</p>

<p>
Therefore,
</p>

<p>
<me>
x = {6}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>x^2+6 x-72=0</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>6</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>